org.safs.tools.logs.processor

Class XMLSaxToJUnitXMLHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.xml.sax.helpers.DefaultHandler
      • org.safs.tools.logs.processor.XMLSaxAbstractHandler
        • org.safs.tools.logs.processor.XMLSaxToJUnitHandler
          • org.safs.tools.logs.processor.XMLSaxToJUnitXMLHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.xml.sax.ContentHandler, org.xml.sax.DTDHandler, org.xml.sax.EntityResolver, org.xml.sax.ErrorHandler

    public class XMLSaxToJUnitXMLHandler
extends XMLSaxToJUnitHandler
    Parse SAFS XML Log and convert it to JUnit XML report, such as: 
     <?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
 <testsuites name="a.testcycle.Cycle.runTest" timestamp="06-19-2018 10:44:44" time="16">
   <testsuite name="a.testsuite.Suite.runTest" tests="5" errors="1" failures="2" skipped="1" timestamp="06-19-2018 10:44:44" time="16" >
     <testcase name="case1" classname="a.testcase.Cases1" time="0">
     </testcase>
     <testcase name="case2" classname="a.testcase.Cases1" time="0">
       <skipped message="This test case will be skipped for some reason" details="a.testcase.Cases1.case2" />
     </testcase>
     <testcase name="case3" classname="a.testcase.Cases1" time="0">
       <failure message="benchFile.txt doesn't match actualFile.txt." details="detailed failure message." type="DIFF" line="59"/>
     </testcase>
     <testcase name="case4" classname="a.testcase.Cases1" time="16">
       <failure message="IsComponentExists failed." details="FANTACY_GUI doesn't exist!" type="NON_EXIST" line="72"/>
       <failure message="WaitForGUI failed." details="FANTACY_GUI doesn't exist!" type="TIMEOUT" line="76"/>
     </testcase>
     <testcase name="case5" classname="a.testcase.Cases1" time="0">
       <failed message="null" type="NullPointerException" line="88"/>
     </testcase>
   </testsuite>
 </testsuites>
    Author:
    Lei Wang
